Description:
COMFY FAMILY HOME CLOSE TO EVERYTHING! (Enter via Bailey Rd)
Look no further! This comfortable 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom, low maintenance family home is perfectly located on half an acre close to the local kindergarten, the Cockatoo shops, the Primary School & public transport. Featuring zoned living, there are 2 spacious bedrooms with built in robes off the central kitchen/meals living area & a comfortable Master bedroom with walk in robe & ensuite off the formal lounge & dining areas. The open plan, light filled kitchen has a dishwasher, heaps of bench & storage space & a huge breakfast bar for convenience. This living area also has access to the spacious under cover outdoor entertaining area, perfect for entertaining all year round. There is mains GDH & an Air Conditioner for added comfort, as well as mains water & sewer. Outside there is dual entry, a sealed drive & double carport, a further double lock up shed with concrete floor & power, a veggie patch & fruit trees, all on a fully fenced, useable half acre. This property ticks all the boxes.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!

Description:
A Wonderful Family Home on 1.3 acres with In Law Accommodation
Whether you are looking for a dual occupancy home for the in-laws or one big enough to fit in the whole family, don't let this one pass you by!
Set on a fully fenced 1.3 acre block, this property offers flat usable areas, above ground pool, orchard and plenty of space for kids to run around.
The upper level of the home has large kitchen with dishwasher and adjoining meals area that overlooks the family room.
The central bathroom with separate toilet services the 4 bedrooms, two with built in robes and the third with a huge walk in robe.
The master suite comes complete with air conditioner, walk in robe and double shower in the large ensuite.
The surprisingly spacious ground floor has a huge master bedroom with built in robes, bathroom and utility room, and two living areas with direct access to the garden.
Special features include gas central heating, wrap around verandah's, sealed road access, garden shed, double carport and all services are connected. Situated in a prime location near to shops and schools, but also providing peace and quiet - Bring the in-laws along for an inspection today!
Contact Mick Dolphin for all inspections on 0429 684522.
Mick Dolphin : 0429 684 522

TRADIES PARADISE!
This is a unique opportunity to buy a private & peaceful 1.3 acres just minutes from Cockatoo, with the added convenience of a huge shed to store all your toys & machinery & live in while you build the dream (STCA). Offering a made driveway & a sunny site cut for the home, some of the hard work has already been done for you. The huge shed on the property has a concrete floor, power, water & phone connected & features heaps of garage, storage & living space that will give you plenty of room to hide away from the elements whilst building. Take the opportunity to build the dream & be surrounded by nature without breaking the bank. Call to arrange a private inspection today!

Description:
BE CALM & COMFORTABLE IN THIS 3 BEDROOM HOME
The surrounding trees, the quiet and the calm all contribute to a feeling of relaxation in this elevated Cockatoo home. On a garden block of around 969sqm the classic cream weatherboard facade conceals a warm and inviting space with a generous lounge/dining area comforted by a split system heater/air conditioner and the kitchen has been beautifully renovated with all stainless steel appliances. There are 3 bedrooms including 2 with built in wardrobes plus a very neat family bathroom, separate toilet and a full laundry. Outside you will find a massive covered entertaining deck, tree lined garden and a single carport with
access to the rear set double garage/workshop. Another bonus here is that all services including water, sewerage and gas are fully connected to town supplies, all located within minutes of Cockatoo facilities including buses, Primary School and shops at the town centre.

Description:
Historic Hills Character Home on Almost 1/2 an Acre!
Featuring 2 bedrooms and a sunroom/study which could be converted to a third bedroom (or ensuite) the home is set amongst cottage gardens spanning almost 1/2 an acre (1749m2).
This home is the perfect all-rounder and would suit anybody who is looking for an investment, first home or for those who want to improve on the gorgeous 2 bedroom cottage and extend.
The cottage still retains original features such as hardwood floorboards, pine lining and the original brick fireplaces in the living room and kitchen including cast iron combustion oven.
The kitchen has been updated with the latest stainless steel appliances and has enough room for a dining table. Across the hall is a large storage room or pantry.
With tranquil views of the garden, the living room and dining room offers access to the paved courtyard - ideal for entertaining on balmy summer nights.
Also on offer in this magical home are beautiful lead light windows, gas ducted heating, gas log fire, double carport, garden shed and all services are connected.
Conveniently located close to local primary school, kindergartens, shops, public transport and is only a 15 minute drive to Pakenham.

LUXURY LIVING ON A GRAND SCALE!
Nestled on 1/2 an acre this large family home offers plenty of space & comfort for you & your family. Boasting large 4 bedrooms, master that offers a full ensuite and WIR, 2 large open plan living areas, cathedral ceilings, stunning modern kitchen with dishwasher, gas ducted heating and 3 split system heating and cooling units that provide year round comfort. Verandahs surround the home & provide an elevated view so you can sit back relax & watch the world go by.

The property is fully fenced, has all services connected, 9000 litres of water for the garden & located at the end of a no through road, your peace & privacy is assured - call us & inspect today...

Description:
MODERN STORYBOOK ON A COTTAGE BLOCK WITH GREAT SHED
This pretty as a picture, storybook home is situated on a manageable 795m2 block of flat land and is ideal for downsizers, investors or first home buyers.
Situated in a quiet no-through road not far from the main street of Cockatoo the home features two good sized bedrooms and living area with kitchen opening onto a fantastic deck.
The central bathroom is larger than you would expect. Upstairs is the master retreat which is large with potential for a second living area or home office. Special features include split system and ducted heating, a flat fully fenced yard and beautiful cottage gardens.
At the rear of the home is a fantastic high span double garage with workshop, mezzanine level, power, water, concrete floor and remote door - ideal for the tradie or as a workshop or storage for the boat or caravan.
This well-loved home with cathedral ceilings throughout is ready to move into straight away. Character-filled both inside and out, you will enjoy many relaxing afternoons on the decking, overlooking your beautiful surrounds as you listen to the sounds of nature on your doorstep.
Don't miss the perfect opportunity to move into a quiet spot on this flat block - Be Quick.
Call Mick Dolphin on 0429 684522 to arrange your inspection.

Description:
'BIBBENLUKE' A BEAUTIFUL COUNTRY HOME ON AROUND 3000SQM
The peace and quiet grabs you here - with nothing but the rustle of trees to disturb the air you can't help but feel relaxed and at ease in the home set on around 3,000sqm (3/4 acre approx.). From its remote operated gates that open to reveal a tree lined driveway, 'Bibbenluke' sits amidst lovely gardens with basement double garage and additional parking area. Up the stairs you find a vast terrace for relaxing and entertaining before you enter the home that has been substantially improved in recent years. Warm colours and gorgeous hardwood floors enhance the lounge and adjoining family area as well as the dining room and amazing show kitchen with granite bench tops and a massive 1200mm stainless steel dual oven/stove. There are 4 bedrooms as well as a dual entry family bathroom with ensuite style access from the master bedroom plus 2 separate powder rooms and the comfort of gas ducted heating. And within 5 minutes you can access the shops, parks and primary school at central Cockatoo while Emerald town centre is just a short drive away.

Description:
'Mill Cottage'- Renovated, Flat Block, Subdivision Potential (STCA)
Simply not a thing to do to, just walk in and enjoy life.
This gorgeous character home in a past life was a sawmiller's cottage. Renovated to an exacting standard the home is sure to please and offers 4 bedrooms, the large master which includes a full ensuite and walk through robe. The home also features a stunning modern kitchen with quality stainless steel appliances including dishwasher and adjoining dining area plus a separate and spacious lounge featuring polished floorboards and picture windows. Special features include gas heating, claw foot bath, large deck, a fresh and modern colour scheme and polished hardwood floors. Outside offers plenty of room to move with a totally useable sunny block, double carport and single garage with concrete floor and power.
There is a circular driveway, sealed road access, plus a chook pen and plenty of room for a vegie patch.
All this with Residential 1 Zoning and all services connected on a sealed road gives a good case for subdivision too (STCA).
Within easy reach of shops, schools and transport.
Your lifestyle awaits - be quick!
